 # NOTE : if some dependecies packages is 
 # not installed when installing any app it 
 # would fail to install it with rpm

-it gives you error and tell to install the debendencies packages manually

- so yum solve that problem

- we can tell yum that we have packages downloaded to come with its pk-debendencies and install it successfuly


[ command: yum localinstall rpm-file-path ]


[root@localhost]# yum localinstall httpd-2.4.6-45.e17.centos.x86â€”64.rpm

----------------------------------------------------------------------------


- if we have an new package and want to 
upgrade the installed one


[ command : rpm -Uvh rpm-file-path ]


--------------------------------------------------------------------------

[ command: rpm -fvh path-rpm-file ]

-this command used in updating the package 
put the only have an old version installed

-----------------------------------------------------------------

# if we have file and want to know witch 
# package created it

[ command : yum provides path-file ]


